 and European missionaries were less equal and more fractious than ever before. However, the colonial era also brought unprecedented ties between Vietnam and the transnational institutions and culture of global Catholicism, as Vatican reforms to create an independent national Church helped Vietnamese Catholics to reimagine and redefine their relationships to both missionary Catholicism and to colonial rule itself. Much like the myriad revolutionary ideologies and struggles in the name of the Vietnamese nation, this revolution in Vietnamese Catholic life was ultimately ambiguous, even contradictory: it established the foundations for an independent national Church, but it also polarized the place of the new Church in post-colonial Vietnamese politics and society and produced deep divisions between Vietnamese Catholics themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aasian history.  abooks about religion.  abooks for history lovers.  acatholic church.  acatholic history.  achristianity.  acolonial modern vietnam.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aeurope and asia.  aeuropean history.  afrench colonial rule.  ahistory of christianity.  ahome school history books.  aleisure reads.  anonfiction.  apage turner.  apost colonial vietnam.  areligion and politics.  areligion in asia.  areligious studies.  asoutheast asia.  avatican.  avietnam history.  avietnamese catholics.  avietnamese culture.  avietnamese politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027247740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095382640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953826423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953826/origin